{"word":"H98 - אֲגַם - ʼăgam - ag-am' - Pond","slug":"H98","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֲגַם</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼăgam"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ag-am'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Pond"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D2;&#x05DD; - 'a&#x0306;gam</b> - <i>ag-am'</i><p/>From an unused root (meaning to <i>collect</i> as water); a <i>marsh</i>; hence a <i>rush</i> (as growing in swamps); hence a <i>stockade</i> of reeds: - pond, pool, standing [water]."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H100\">H100</a>, <a href=\"#/H99\">H99</a>"}]}